"title": "5089: David, significance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5089: david, significance of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>David was instrumental in the establishment of Jerusalem as the centre of Israel's worship. Through David's personal rule, God exercised his own kingship over his people. David thus foreshadowed the Messiah, who would spring from his royal line.</p>\n<h2>The historical significance of David</h2>\n<h3>The establishment of Jerusalem as the centre of worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:1-2Sam6:11\">2SA 6:1–6:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:1-1Chr13:14\">1CH 13:1–13:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:12-2Sam6:15\">2SA 6:12–6:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:25-1Chr15:28\">1CH 15:25–15:28</a></p>\n<h3>Preparations for building the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:2-1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:2–28:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:1-2Sam7:7\">2SA 7:1–7:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:1-1Chr17:6\">1CH 17:1–17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:17-1Kgs8:19\">1KI 8:17–8:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:7-2Chr6:9\">2CH 6:7–6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:1-1Chr22:19\">1CH 22:1–22:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:4-1Chr23:5\">1CH 23:4–23:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:1\">1CH 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:12\">1CH 26:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:1-1Chr29:5\">1CH 29:1–29:5</a></p>\n<h2>The spiritual significance of David</h2>\n<h3>The son of God and chosen king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:6-Ps2:7\">PSA 2:6–2:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>An eternal priest</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:4\">PSA 110:4</a></p>\n<h3>A sign of God's final victory</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:8-Ps2:11\">PSA 2:8–2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1-Ps110:3\">PSA 110:1–110:3</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant with David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:11-2Sam7:16\">2SA 7:11–7:16</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:10-1Chr17:14\">1CH 17:10–17:14</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:11-1Kgs11:13\">1KI 11:11–11:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:19\">2KI 8:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:7\">2CH 21:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:1-Ps89:37\">PSA 89:1–89:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:12\">PSA 132:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:3\">ISA 55:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:17\">JER 33:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:21-Ezek37:28\">EZK 37:21–37:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:22-Acts13:23\">ACT 13:22–13:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:32-Acts13:37\">ACT 13:32–13:37</a></p>\n<h2>David as a type of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as the Son of David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5\">JER 23:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23-Ezek34:24\">EZK 34:23–34:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:5\">ISA 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:1\">MAT 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:23\">MAT 12:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:9\">MAT 21:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:30\">MAT 20:30</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:46-Mark10:47\">MRK 10:46–10:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:35-Luke18:38\">LUK 18:35–18:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:41-John7:42\">JHN 7:41–7:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's kingship is linked with David's kingship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32-Luke1:33\">LUK 1:32–1:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:7\">ISA 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:5\">ISA 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:41-Matt22:46\">MAT 22:41–22:46</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:35-Mark12:37\">MRK 12:35–12:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:41-Luke20:44\">LUK 20:41–20:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a></p>",
